   13 December 2018  |  By Philippe  |  In Wildlife

What Model for Wildlife Conservation in Africa: private reserve, conservancy,
national park?

   Wildlife conservation through the creation of national parks and
   reserves is a necessity to protect natural habitats from human
   activities. In 1872, Yellowstone was the first national park, many
   others followed since. Nowadays, several management models exist for
   conservation in Africa with heterogenic results. Numerous threats
   pressure natural habitats: poachers, conflicts with farmers and
   economic […]

